item.description: "I will end 'don't ask-don't tell,'" Obama said at the annual dinner of the Human Rights Campaign, a gay civil rights advocacy group. He did not give a timetable for the repeal of the law passed by Congress in 1993 and signed by President Bill Clinton, who also promised to repeal the ban on homosexuals in the military but was blunted by opposition

item.title: [+909] U.S. Healthcare: The Canadian Perspective
item.description: In the 1960s, the U.S. chose public coverage for only elderly and the poor, while Canada opted for a universal program. As a policy analyst, I know there are lessons to be learned, but, as a Canadian with lots of American friends and relatives, I am saddened that Americans seem incapable of learning them.

item.title: [+454] 10 Devices That Can Do It All (Pics)
item.description: TV chef Alton Brown has it right: Unitaskers – specialty devices that only perform one function – have no place in the kitchen. And single-purpose gadgets have no place in your pocket. Though there are exceptions for purebred machines that far outperform their all-in-one counterparts, most gadgets need to earn their keep in a multitude of ways.
